### Run login.http first — it sets the global {{token}} variable.

### 1st call -> CACHE MISS: Hibernate SQL appears in patient-service logs,
###             result is written to Redis under key "patientsList::all"
GET http://localhost:4004/api/patients
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 2nd call -> CACHE HIT: no SQL in the logs, and the cache logger prints
###             "Cache entry for key 'all' found in cache 'patientsList'"
GET http://localhost:4004/api/patients
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get one patient by ID (fills the "patients" cache — call it twice too)
GET http://localhost:4004/api/patients/b6d657fd-a49d-47c6-bafa-226d48e594c5
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### -> Authorization: Bearer {{token}} -> to send Auth token for JwtValidation - Filter
### -> token must start from Bearer as we defind in business logic of JwtValidationFilter
### -> Inspect Redis directly: docker exec -it redis redis-cli KEYS '*'